For pros, no practicality. 1. Pitch, why is it locked at the original? (Or I dunno how to work this thing?) 2. Songs load slower then the one playing as master, and I can't beat match with pitch fader, critically flawed design. 3. The UI is not really user friendly, why the sliders are snapped to middle? It's like I am either on 124 or 128, no 126, 127...And the difference between a BPM of 124.00 to 124.20 is that you already hear fallout on the third beat, what's the point? 4. Add beat jump maybe? 5. Beatwave - add a vertical line every 32 beat.  For amateur, you can't learn the essence of DJing with this one, just for home party fun is cool tho, for that price? Nah ah.

And  thanks for using edjing Pro!

Unfortunately, you can't import Google Play songs on the app: actually, your songs have to be located in the native 'Music' file of your device, and Google Play songs aren't in this file.

Our technical team is doing the best to get round this restriction!
Thanks in advance for your understanding.

content: This app is actually awesome. The FX and everything works perfectly. It has a very nice UI and it's rather easy to use. It's disappointing for everyone. Then again, I'm sure they'll fix it. Eventually.

Annoying notifications. App is a rarely used novelty. Tools aren't powerful enough to do what I want editing and I use dedicated music app for general use. And the worst crime is the activity in system processes when not in use. That last one is an unacceptable offence that costs this app removal. Probably just license check but I'm over apps doing that, 20 apps constantly checking. Maybe 100!!!  No thanks. No internet and apps fail check and I get angry. That's why I removed poweramp and ES pro.
